sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Risk assessment and expedited path
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Company, Clean Payment History)

    alt Low-Risk Customer (All criteria met)
        F-->>S: Auto-Approved (Expedited - No Director Review)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited path)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk Customer (Any criteria failed)
        F->>F: Escalate to Finance Director
        F-->>S: Director Approval (24h SLA)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (standard path)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    end
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Replaced the single Finance approval step with a risk assessment decision point that evaluates three criteria (credit score >750, verified company status, clean payment history). Added an alt/else block: low-risk customers matching all criteria bypass Finance Director review and proceed directly to expedited account provisioning, while high-risk customers follow the existing escalation path through Finance Director approval with the 24h SLA.